@WeichenXu123 I think it will increase adoption of mlflow if additional container runtimes were supported.

As an example: Many people are forced to use a non-proprietary CR like containerd instead of Docker, because their company doesn't want to pay the the enterprise license for Docker Desktop.

Kubernetes made the transition from Docker to containerd and this decision was generally viewed as a good one.

@marcelatoffernet Sounds reasonable.
Is docker community version not allowed to be used in company ?

CC @dbczumar Thoughts ?

@WeichenXu123 Please see [their pricing tos](https://www.docker.com/pricing/faq/) at the "How will Docker enforce the new subscription terms for Docker Desktop?" section.

Business with annual revenue over 10mil$ face legal issues using any docker tooling without licences. 

I know a fair number of business who are trying to wean themselves off Docker before they hit this limit.
